FT  28 JUL 94 / Jury in BCCI fraud trial retires
The Old Bailey jury in the final trial brought in the UK over the collapsed
Bank of Credit and Commerce International retired to consider its verdict
yesterday.
Mr Imran Imam, a former BCCI accounts officer, is accused of helping to
fraudulently boost the bank's profits by almost Dollars 250m by manipulating
loan accounts.
Mr Imam denies six charges including conspiring to conceal documents,
conspiring to falsify accounts and furnishing false information.
